The students enjoyed the film, so I showed them additional video clips of contemporary Jamaican Maroons performing or explaining their lifeways. ; ;
Another student wrote that “hearing fromlocal Maroons such as Colonel Frank Lumsden and Delano Douglas give the world a better idea of Maroons as lovers of nature and defenders of their cultural history in comparison with racist, colonialist generalizations that we read” (student response paper).
The student author has given permission for this statement to be shared. Other students agreed that the paratextual materials “made Maroon history real” for them, and when they returned to the course texts, they better understood the proud rebels omitted almost entirely from Child’s text.
